Peel and chop the @red onion{2}(peeled and chopped into 1cm pieces). Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{4}(peeled and finely chopped). Grate the zest of the @lemon{2} into a #bowl{} and squeeze the juice in to the #jug{} too, set this aside for later.

Put the @British chicken thighs{8} in a bowl with the @paprika{2%tsp}, @ground cumin{2%tsp}, half the garlic, a third of the lemon juice/zest mixture and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Mix it around making sure all the chicken gets a good coating.

> Tip: The best way to do this is to use your hands but do make sure you wash them properly after handling raw meat.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #saucepan{} over a medium heat. Add the onion and remaining garlic along with some @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until the onion is soft. Add the @basmati rice{2} and another pinch of salt, mix well and then add @water{700%ml} to the pan. Bring to the boil, stirring to make sure it doesn't all stick together. Once the rice has come to the boil, turn down to a low heat, cover and leave to simmer for ~{10%minutes}. Once the 10 mins is up turn off the heat and let it sit for a further ~{10%minutes} - don't peek under the lid until the 20 mins are up!

While the rice is cooking, start on the chicken! Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a medium hot #frying pan{} and add the chicken. Cook the chicken for ~{4%minutes} on each side until it is a lovely brown colour. While the chicken is cooking, boil a small pan of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} and add the @peas{2}. Boil for ~{1 1/2%minutes}, drain and set these aside for later.

Turn the chicken over again, cover the pan with a #lid{} and turn the heat to low. Cook for a further ~{5%minutes}. Once the chicken is cooked, take the lid off, add the @honey{2%tbsp}, half the remaining lemon juice/zest and @water{100%ml}. Season with a good pinch of salt and a grind of pepper and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} until you have a lovely sticky sauce.

Roughly chop your @flat leaf parsley{5%sprigs} and set aside a little for garnish. When the rice is ready fluff it up with a #fork{}, add the parsley, peas, remaining lemon juice/zest and stir it all together.

Slice the chicken to about 1 1/2 cm thick and serve the rice topped with the chicken, sticky sauce and any leftover parsley. Enjoy!